gulation. This comprehensive treatment approach addresses the core issues of BPD, aiming to enhance coping mechanisms and foster healthier relationships.\",2\r\n111,ALBERT,,1\r\n774,DIALECTICAL BEHAVIOR THERAPY,A type of psychotherapy that is effective in treating borderline personality disorder,1\r\n770,SCHIZOID PERSONALITY DISORDER,\"**Schizoid Personality Disorder** is a personality disorder characterized by a pervasive pattern of detachment from social relationships and a restricted range of emotional expression. This condition typically manifests in early adulthood, leading individuals to appear emotionally distant and indifferent to social interactions. The disorder is best treated with supportive therapy, which aims to help individuals manage their symptoms and improve their quality of life. While the disorder presents challenges in forming and maintaining relationships, therapeutic interventions can provide valuable assistance in navigating these difficulties.\",2\r\n773,SUPPORTIVE THERAPY,A type of psychotherapy that is effective in treating certain personality disorders,1\r\n2139,FRONTAL LOBE TUMOR,,1\r\n2140,PERSONALITY CHANGES,,2\r\n\n\n-----Relationships-----\nhuman_readable_id,source,target,description,combined_degree\r\n933,ANOREXIA NERVOSA,COGNITIVE BEHAVIORAL THERAPY,Anorexia nervosa is often treated with cognitive behavioral therapy,36\r\n935,BULIMIA NERVOSA,COGNITIVE BEHAVIORAL THERAPY,Bulimia nervosa is often treated with cognitive behavioral therapy,25\r\n2456,EATING DISORDER,ANOREXIA NERVOSA,Anorexia nervosa is a type of eating disorder characterized by intentional restriction of food intake,18\r\n2861,PERSONALITY DISORDER,PARANOID PERSONALITY DISORDER,Paranoid Personality Disorder is a specific type of Personality Disorder,18\r\n934,ANOREXIA NERVOSA,ANTIDEPRESSANT MEDICATION,Anorexia nervosa is often treated with a combination of psychotherapy and antidepressant medication,17\r\n2462,ANOREXIA NERVOSA,GENETIC FACTORS,\"Genetic factors, such as 